subsection.p:
Before , we noted that a percent increase of r (in decimal form) corresponds to a growth factor of b = 1 + r. A percent decrease of r corresponds to a decay factor of b = 1 - r. In Part B of , each millimeter of plastic reduced the amount of light by 25, so r = 0.25, and the decay factor for the function P(x) is
\begin{align*}
b \amp = 1 - r \\
\amp= 1 - 0.25 = 0.75
\end{align*}

